org.piwik.java.tracking

Class PiwikJsonObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.piwik.java.tracking.PiwikJsonObject

  • public class PiwikJsonObject
extends Object
    Object representing the custom variable array required by some Piwik query parameters. An array is represented by an object that has the index of the entry as the key (1 indexed) and a 2 entry array representing a custom key and custom value as the value.

      • toString

        public String toString()
        Produces the JSON string representing this object.

        For example, if the following values were put into the object

        ("key1", "value1") and ("key2", "value2")

        {"1": ["key1", "value1"], "2": ["key2": "value2"]}

        could be produced. Note that there is no guarantee about the ordering of the produced JSON based. The following JSON is also valid and could also be produced:

        {"1": ["key2", "value2"], "2": ["key1": "value1"]} .
